Package: prefviz
Title: Visualizes Preference Data via Ternary Plots in Two and Higher dimensions
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
  person("Linh", "Ngo", email = "Linh.Ngo2@monash.edu", role = c("aut", "cre")),
  person("Dianne", "Cook", email = "DiCook@monash.edu", role = "aut", comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-3813-7155")),
  person("Damjan", "Vukcevic", email = "damjan.vukcevic@monash.edu", role = "aut", comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0001-7780-9586")))
Description: Visualises preference and ranking data by extending traditional 
    ternary plots to support high-dimensional simplexes. The package provides methods to 
    transform compositional data into coordinates suitable for 2D and high-dimensional
    ternary plots (see Cook & Laa (2024) <https://dicook.github.io/mulgar_book/>). 
    Compatibility with interactive visualization packages such as 'plotly'
    or 'detourr' allows users to explore high-dimensional preference structures dynamically.
